The following steps are performed with rule build-vertx
-Download the vert.x source code from github
-Apply a patch
-Update the library with the new version and compile the changed library
-Upload the changed library to our internal maven repository for distribution
-Copy changed source code of the library back to this directory for reference

To create a new version
-Open the ruleset and edit the rule build-vertx
-Change the VERTX_VERSION and VERTX_TARGET_VERSION
-Run bob/bob build-vertx

Afterwards, check in the ruleset with the updated versions and the changed source files
stored in vertx-trace/edited_vertx_files
